# Explicit path → owner mapping for files whose history does not yield a
# single, correct owner via mechanical derivation. This is the escape hatch
# for genuine ambiguity — not a general-purpose ownership registry.
#
# Format: `path  owner-branch` (whitespace-separated). Comments begin with `#`.
#
# Each override silences the double-introduction warning for the named path
# and causes ownership derivation to return the declared owner instead of
# the mechanically-derived one. `cascade check` flags overrides whose owner
# branch is invalid (error) or whose declared owner matches what derivation
# would produce anyway (info — safe to remove).
#
# See cascade/docs/ownership.md.

# Pre-cascade double introductions: the same test files landed on several
# ephemeral/feature branches before the branching model was established.
# They are legitimately core files; derivation currently picks an arbitrary
# first-parent match.
src/dir-fingerprint.test.ts    main
src/interaction/session.ts     main
src/mount-security.test.ts     main
src/test-helpers.ts            main
